  <Summary>In New Orleans, Lisa Boudreaux, a freshman at Arcane Bayou University, juggles college life with her fascination for local folklore. Her world changes when she finds an old trinket in the French Quarter, sparking visions that reveal her lineage as a descendant of Papa Legba. Guided by a professor who is also a Voodoo houngan, Lisa learns to harness her newfound abilities. She discovers that her awakening isn't by chance, but a call to embrace her heritage and face the profound changes it brings. Together, they unravel her destiny and a conspiracy, placing her at the heart of a transformative journey intertwined with the echoes of her ancestral past.

